cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the impact of mobility on wireless networks and proposes methods to improve resource allocation and mobility management. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses mathematical models to derive the distribution and mean of sojourn time in multi-tier cellular networks. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the relation between mean sojourn time and other mobility-related performance metrics, which can be useful in designing multiagent systems for network management. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes methods to improve resource allocation and mobility management in wireless networks, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the impact of user velocity and network parameters on the sojourn time, which is a performance metric of wireless networks.
